39:46.619 --> 39:49.356
- You did the other day.

39:49.389 --> 39:51.623
- You've been making
a lot of jabs at me.

39:51.657 --> 39:54.927
It's like a bully.
- Stop it right now.

39:54.960 --> 39:56.528
<i>When I did that interview,</i>

39:56.563 --> 39:58.597
they asked me how's it
going, you know, with the girls?

39:58.630 --> 40:02.501
It was right after lip kit
launch so I was heated.

40:02.534 --> 40:05.771
- You came after me first.
- I didn't come after you.

40:05.804 --> 40:07.706
I said little things that
you were right next to me

40:07.740 --> 40:08.974
when I said them

40:09.900 --> 40:10.376
so they weren't like
coming after you.

40:10.409 --> 40:11.710
- No, no, no. No,
no, no, no. No.

40:11.744 --> 40:13.130
Here's my real
issue with Garcelle.

40:13.460 --> 40:15.382
If you've got a
problem, really voice it.

40:15.414 --> 40:16.849
But if you don't,

40:16.882 --> 40:20.452
don't come up with things
just to be provocative

40:20.487 --> 40:22.621
because you think that it
makes you more interesting.

40:22.655 --> 40:24.824
I thought you and I
moved past our issues.

40:24.858 --> 40:27.726
- Am I not allowed to
have my own opinion?

40:27.760 --> 40:29.561
- Of course, you are.
- Whether you like it or not.

40:29.596 --> 40:31.639
- I would love to
hear your opinion.

40:31.969 --> 40:31.998
- Can I have my opinion?
- 100% you can.

40:32.320 --> 40:33.666
- I love when people
have their opinions.

40:33.699 --> 40:35.099
- Everyone's allowed
to have their opinion.

40:35.349 --> 40:36.802
- It doesn't feel like because
my opinion only works if it--

40:36.835 --> 40:37.871
If it satisfies you.

40:37.903 --> 40:39.606
- No, no, no, no, no, no, no.

40:39.639 --> 40:41.940
- If it goes against
how you feel then it's,

40:41.974 --> 40:43.108
I can't have that opinion.

40:43.143 --> 40:45.744
- I speak four languages.
- Good for you.

40:45.778 --> 40:48.914
- And that doesn't make
sense in any one of 'em.

40:50.150 --> 40:51.479
<i>If you've got an issue</i>

40:51.480 --> 40:53.530
<i>or you think I talk
too much, tell me.</i>

40:53.860 --> 40:56.856
Don't mask it with a
passive aggressive comment.

40:56.889 --> 40:58.824
<i>It doesn't make any sense.</i>

41:09.768 --> 41:11.838
- Do we need to get
up and go over there?

41:17.177 --> 41:18.277
- I just wonder,

41:18.311 --> 41:21.547
do you genuinely feel like
anyone's coming after you?

41:21.581 --> 41:23.682
- Well, I felt like
you came after me

41:23.717 --> 41:25.952
and no one stood
up for me but you.

41:25.985 --> 41:27.820
- Oh, did you?
- Yeah.

41:27.853 --> 41:29.755
I'm going to help
because--because

41:29.789 --> 41:32.726
I'm just a bystander,
but I heard that you heard

41:32.759 --> 41:35.494
don't talk about this
but you were not there.

41:35.527 --> 41:37.931
- I was in the car.
- That is correct.

41:39.565 --> 41:40.900
- No one ever takes my side.

41:40.934 --> 41:42.100
<i>[dramatic sting]</i>

41:42.101 --> 41:45.672
- No one ever takes her side?
- Yeah.

41:45.704 --> 41:46.940
- I don't believe it's true

41:46.972 --> 41:49.107
that you're an
outsider in this group

41:49.108 --> 41:51.110
or people don't make an
effort. I don't believe that's true.

41:51.143 --> 41:53.780
- I said that's
how I feel. <i>If I say</i>

41:53.813 --> 41:56.715
I feel like I'm an
outsider, that's how I feel.

41:56.750 --> 41:58.851
<i>They could have had my
back but no one spoke up.</i>

41:58.885 --> 41:59.786
<i>No one said anything.</i>

41:59.818 --> 42:02.549
<i>That's one of the
things with Rinna.</i>

42:02.550 --> 42:04.556
<i>Although she wanted
to repair our friendship,</i>

42:04.590 --> 42:05.824
<i>she never stood up for me.</i>

42:05.858 --> 42:09.596
